{
  "doc_id": "33719",
  "text": "The TG and TC levels in plasma were measured by colorimetric slides using the FUJI DRICHEM analyzer (DRI-CHEM 3500, FujiFilm Medical Co. Ltd., Tokyo, Japan). The liver sections (100-200 mg) were homogenized in phosphate buffer solution (pH7.4) by a polytron (PT 3100, KINEMATICA, Inc., Littau/Lucerne, Switzerland), and crude lipid extracts were obtained by the method described by Bligh and Dyer [CITATION_1] . TG levels were measured using crude lipid samples by the Wako TG E test kit (Wako Pure Chemical Industries, Ltd., Osaka, Japan).",
